[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains 219.

Data by country, area, or territory for 03 Feb 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20Feb3_1612450012.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 50.2% of daily case numbers and 35.3% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 45.98 million cases. The USA remains the most heavily affected country, followed by Brazil and Argentina (reporting more than 10 000 cases in the past 24 hours); 8 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Colombia, Mexico, Peru, Honduras, Canada, Chile, Bolivia, and Cuba), and an additional 7 countries (Panama, Paraguay, Puerto Rico, Venezuela, Guatemala, Dominican Republic, and Uruguay) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 33.5% of daily case numbers and 50.0% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 34.65 million. Countries not reporting cases include Spain, Belgium, Israel, Switzerland (4 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others. France is the most heavily affected, followed by the UK and Russia reporting more than 10 000 cases in the last 24 hours. Another 15 countries reported more than 1000 cases (Italy, Turkey, Czech Republic, Germany, Sweden, Portugal, Greece, Poland, Netherlands, Ukraine, Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Romania, and Ireland), and an additional 12 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases (Croatia, Belarus, Austria, Albania, Georgia, Bulgaria, Hungary, Moldova, Latvia, Estonia, Albania, and Lithuania).

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 5.7% of daily case numbers and 3.6% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.73 million cases. Iran maintains its dominance, reporting close to 6800 cases, followed by UAE, Lebanon, Pakistan, Libya, and Tunisia. Iraq, Jordan, Kuwait, Palestinian Authority, Egypt, and Bahrain reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 2.7% of daily case numbers and 5.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 2.60 million cases. South Africa maintains its dominance, with over 2600 cases followed by Nigeria and Zambia. Mozambique, Ghana, and Malawi reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Botswana, Madagascar, and Mauritania, among others, did not report any newly confirmed cases in the preceding 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.9% of daily case numbers and 1.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 1.44 million cases. Malaysia reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 3400 cases), followed by Japan, Philippines, South Korea, and China.

- The South East Asia region reported 6.0% of the daily newly reported cases and 3.6% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 12.92 million cases. India is dominant having reported over 11 000 cases, followed by Indonesia reporting over 10 000 cases, Thailand, Sri Lanka, Bangladesh, Maldives, Myanmar, and Nepal.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 3 Feb 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

